From: Mono OpenWrt <mono-openwrt@local>
Subject: selinux-policy: allow Mono OpenWrt bring-up paths

Cover the first set of SELinux permissive-mode denials seen on the Mono
Gateway Development Kit without granting broad tmpfs access. In particular,
label odhcpd's current temporary state paths so rpcd can consume the lease
file through the existing odhcpd tmp-file policy, label libsensors
configuration so htop can read temperature data without broad /etc directory
access, let htop read the sysfs metadata it needs as a process viewer, and let
ucode transition to the existing iproute2 and wireguard domains instead of
running those tools in ucode.subj.

